{"tid":1961390,"cid":5,"subCid":0,"title":"Zoom加密原來會send返畀中國","createTime":"2020-04-06T18:38:34.000Z","updateTime":"2020-04-07T05:00:09.000Z","uid":178187,"like":20,"dislike":2,"uniUserReply":17,"replies":[{"pid":"57165e7b5079bbd357d9f00f3da07fc6a2b26ab0","tid":1961390,"uid":178187,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-04-06T18:38:34.000Z","msg":"In end-to-end encryption, normally the key is generated and stored on your smartphone or laptop. However, Zoom will manage the keys over the company's servers, a few of which are based in China, according to Citizen Lab.<br />\nBy <br />\nMichael Kan<br />\n <br />\n3 Apr 2020, 8:50 p.m.<br />\nZoom says it offers end-to-end encryption on your video conferences to help ward off spying, but don&rsquo;t believe it. The San Jose-based company is not only holding on to the encryption keys, but also sending them to China in some cases, according to a watchdog group.<br />\n<br />\n<br />\n<img src=\"https://na.cx/i/qr3pw18.png\" data-thumbnail-src=\"https://i.lih.kg/thumbnail?u=https%3A%2F%2Fna.cx%2Fi%2Fqr3pw18.png&h=63899385&s={SIZE}\" /><br />\n<br />\n<br />\n<br />\n<a href=\"https://uk.pcmag.com/antispam/125528/zooms-encryption-keys-are-sometimes-being-sent-to-china-report-finds\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Fuk.pcmag.com%2Fantispam%2F125528%2Fzooms-encryption-keys-are-sometimes-being-sent-to-china-report-finds&d=oVNa%2F3rGcR5VJv77DJ2le%2FS0i%2BS8%2FYHgnNJfWlbrK%2Bw%3D&h=ba097b94\" target=\"_blank\">https://uk.pcmag.com/antispam/125528/zooms-encryption-keys-are-sometimes-being-sent-to-china-report-finds</a>"},{"pid":"470732b07fc4a92e63deef1380dcd1c3c0b0c9dd","tid":1961390,"uid":178187,"like":4,"dislike":0,"score":4,"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2020-04-06T18:43:29.000Z","msg":"Zoom老闆<br />\n<br />\n<img src=\"https://na.cx/i/FPTMLo4.png\" data-thumbnail-src=\"https://i.lih.kg/thumbnail?u=https%3A%2F%2Fna.cx%2Fi%2FFPTMLo4.png&h=bca8f6b7&s={SIZE}\" />"},{"pid":"9b434902ccbe137a19ccb